# Theme contrast (Vintage Radio)

When editing `gui/theme.py`, `gui/themes/*.py`, or widget QSS that hardcodes colours:

1. **Pair rule**: every `*_BG`, `*_GRAD_*`, or panel surface needs a documented text/icon token tested on it.
2. **All three palettes** (`vintage`, `high_contrast`, `colorblind`) must pass `pytest tests/gui/test_theme_contrast.py` — not just high_contrast. Add any new theme to `_ALL_THEMES` in the test.
3. Use `gui/themes/contrast_utils.contrast_ratio(fg, bg)` when unsure.
4. After palette changes, always run:
   ```bash
   pytest tests/gui/test_theme_contrast.py tests/gui/test_ui_scale_and_themes.py -q
   ```
5. Monochromatic icons must pass **4.5:1** (text threshold). Test every distinct `(icon_color, surface)` pair individually — the same icon on a selected row vs an unselected row are different pairs.
6. If station and track scrollbar rails have different luminances, use `SB_STA_THUMB_GRAD_TOP` (dark rail) separately from `SB_THUMB_GRAD_TOP` (light rail).
7. Project copy: `.cursor/rules/design-system-accessibility.mdc` (openable in this repo).

**Vintage accent buttons**: icon/text use dark `#1E1610` on bright-orange surfaces (≥ 4.5:1). Button gradient must be dark enough for the chosen foreground. Do NOT use cream/white fg on a mid-light orange top stop.
**Colorblind accent buttons**: icon/text use `#121212` on orange surfaces (8:1+).
**High-contrast accent buttons**: icon/text are `#FFFFFF` on the dark-blue gradient.
